title: 1 bedroom lowery hill apartment
posting_body: ['This is a top (2nd) floor, 1 bedroom corner apartment with a walk-in closet, built-in bookcase, a living room, a dining room, plenty of windows and wood floors is in a charming old building a few blocks from bus lines.', 'This is close to uptown without the noise and congestion of uptown.', 'The apartment is in a quiet location, yet in an exciting neighborhood about 1 mile north of Calhoun Square in Uptown and about 2 blocks off Hennepin and Franklin.', 'From this location you can easily access Highways 35W, 94 and 394.', 'We are in the Lowry Hill/Kenwood neighborhood and the surrounding area has great historical buildings.', 'Enjoy living in a community that really stands out.', 'Within the Calhoun-Isles community, Lowry Hill/Kenwood sits just west of downtown Minneapolis.', 'The population of this area provides a close-knit community of approximately 4,000 residents.', 'Within about a 6- to 15-minute walking distance, you have access to any one of the following Parks & Recreation locations, and walking/jogging/biking paths: Thomas Lowry Park, Mueller Park, Cowles Conservatory, Minneapolis Sculpture Garden, Lake of the Isles, Kenwood Park.', 'There are also fine-dining and casual restaurants, and a Sebastian Joes within walking distance.', "There are grocery stores, including Kowalski's Market, and endless restaurants and entertainment options in close vicinity.", 'On-site washer/dryer, Cable and US Internet services are available.', 'Gas, water and heat are paid.', 'Early move in possible', 'Available September 1st', '$1050 rent per month', '$1050 security deposit']
